nt (NPD) projects in collaboration with Supplier Quality Assurance (SQA) and Engineering teams.  Conducted re-sourcing initiatives, consolidated procurement efforts, and standardized components to meet predetermined targets.  Identified and cultivated prospective vendors while evaluating supplier performance against various criteria, including on-time delivery, quality enhancement, service excellence, costeffectiveness, and credit terms.  Led the implementation of an ERP system, specifically E-Purchase, to streamline procurement processes.  Conducted competitive analyses, carried out rejection assessments, and initiated corrective actions with suppliers to align costs with market trends. This included managing inventory control and planning for efficient delivery.  Maintained oversight over supplier communication, ensuring timely deliveries and conducting quality inspections, while also ensuring prompt payment processing.  Established and enforced effective procurement schedules and proactively implemented costsaving strategies throughout the procurement cycle.  Actively engaged in cost optimization efforts and conducted contract negotiations to maximize value for the organization. TATA AUTOCOMP SYSTEMS LTD. (Interiors & Plastics Div.) Pune, MH May’08 – June’11 Tata Auto Comp Systems Limited (Tata Auto Comp) provides products and services to the Indian and Global automotive OEMs as well as Tier 1 suppliers. Tata Auto Comp has own capabilities in Automotive Interior & Exterior Plastics, Composites, Sheet Metal Stampings as well as Engineering and Supply Chain. Purchase Officer  Managed the procurement of a total of 400 items across diverse categories, including Plastics Molded, Rubber Machining, Press Fabricated, and Foams.  Oversaw the acquisition of 45 consumable items essential for the Paint Shop and Mold Shop, such as Emery paper and polishing materials.  Coordinated the procurement of all RP Material, along with 20 packaging materials like polybags and bubble bags.  Effectively handled relationships with 60 vendors, both local and from various parts of India.  Conducted monthly material planning and scheduling to align with customer requirements.  Implemented day-to-day planning strategies, maintaining designated Min/Max inventory levels in adherence to a JIT (Just-in-Time) system.  Spearheaded cost-saving projects through Value Analysis/Value Engineering (VA/VE) proposals and resourcing efforts.  Fostered strong collaboration between quality and suppliers to swiftly resolve any qualityrelated issues.  Led a team of three members as the in-charge of Non-production Item procurement.  Managed the end-to-end procurement process, which involved processing purchase requisitions, soliciting quotations, and generating and releasing purchase orders using ORACLE/SAP on a Procure-to-Pay (P2P) basis.  Monitored delivery schedules closely, maintaining regular communication with vendors to ensure timely material and service delivery in line with agreed-upon purchase order terms.  Applied organizational guidelines to select suitable vendors for procurement.  Tracked costs diligently and met or exceeded cost reduction targets.  Actively participated in competitive bidding / e-auctions as a member of the central Purchase team, contributing to cost reduction programs, vendor rationalization, expediting new product development, optimizing costs, and negotiating contracts. Exide Industries Ltd., Pune Jul’11 – Sep’11 Poonam Enterprises. Pune June’07 – May’08 | SAP; DIT ( From C-DAC ); Oracle | 2011-2017"}]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\Salil Kulkarni CV.pdf', 'Name: Areas Of Expertise

